    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>as finely as you can</p><p>Dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> in a bowl with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to the bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678179766672-x200.jpg",
