        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>soaked ancho chilli </strong>(can’t handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and all of the <strong>soaking liquid</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>pambazo sauce</strong></p><p>Once the potato has had an initial 6-7 min, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 7-8 min or until the potato is cooked through</p><p>Once cooked through, add 2/3 of the <strong>pambazo sauce </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant – this is your <strong>pambazo filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
